Warden's Quarters

The room is large and spacious, the walls a comforting shade of lavender. A crystal chandelier hangs from the ceiling, and lush pillows sit atop a queen-sized mattress. An electric fireplace at the foot of the bed reminds you of the lodge in Colorado where you and Isabelle spent your honeymoon. A large wedding portait hangs above the fireplace, but your attention is immediately caught by what looks to be a colorful mural spanning across the walls of the bedroom. Flowers of every shade and shape, golden, cinder, magenta, swaying gently to an unseen wind, filling the air with an undetectable fragrance . . . A sliding door opens onto a walk-in bathroom to the west.

You can see a bed, a nightstand, a bookshelf, a Wedding Portrait and a mural.
You can go east or west.
> x wedding portrait

> x wedding portrait
It is a portrait of a young, handsome couple, the type you might see hung with pride on the wall of a photographer's studio. The man is tall and dark, his eyes looking straight at the camera. A small handlebar mustache gives him an air of silliness which clashes with his serious expression. The woman is blonde and lightly freckled, her smiling face turned towards her new husband. There is no date anywhere on the photo.
> x mural

> x mural
You've never seen a bedroom like this before. You lean in closer and feel the uneven texture of the flowers with your fingers; every single one was drawn with paint and brush, with a painstaking care for detail. Almost without realizing it you begin to count the flowers. There are fifty-one in total.
> x bookshelf

> x bookshelf
The shelf is built into the wall, two rows filled to the brim with books. You scan the top row and find Agatha Christie novels that you've never heard of. Gardening handbooks fill the bottom row; you never knew there were so many books about gardening in the world.
