Bedroom (Dr. Carl Schneider)

The room is simple and bare. A single mattress sits atop a derelict frame; the frayed comforter is folded in a perfect, military cube. A solitary bulb reluctantly shines upon a small, wooden desk and a larger chair. There is no window in this room either. There is a garden rake leaning against the corner, its teeth choked with dark soil.

You can see a bed, a desk (on which there is a picture frame, And Then There Were None and a pair of glasses), a chair and a rake.
