Suddenly, you find yourself face-to-face with the floor. The ground is shaking and turning, rumbling like an angry beast. Earthquake! A childhood in California has familiarized you with this particular natural disaster, but you've never felt one this powerful before. Just when it feels like the earth might split open, everything stops. You rise shakily to your feet.
