> north
You wave the badge in front of you, and the door slides open on silent tracks. Beyond the doorway, all you see is darkness.

Star Room

You step onto a black walkway and the door closes behind you. You are engulfed by a complete and total darkness. A familiar voice speaks to you from out of this darkness, and for a second you think that it's Isabelle, but it can't be. Isabelle is long dead.

"Welcome to the Star Observation Room of the ARC Two. To give you an immersive experience, the gravity generator in this chamber will be temporarily switched off. We hope you have the best time." As the voice fades, you feel a lightness spread throughout your body, and all the worries and fears you've been carrying suddenly seem to weigh nothing. You take a step forward and you find yourself sailing slowly through the air. Your eyes adjust and you see that you are not alone; you are surrounded by millions of stars, more than you've ever seen before, too many to even imagine counting. You feel as if you are one of them.

You can go north or south.

Finally, you feel at peace . . .

The End of Part Two

